---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — DeviceLab"
  description="DeviceLab ranks laptops, tablets and desktop PCs on six axes with weights you set yourself. No sponsored order, deterministic scoring."
>
  <section class="dl-page-header">
    <div class="dl-eyebrow-hero">DEVICELAB / ABOUT</div>
    <h1>The device leaderboard <br />you can weigh yourself.</h1>
    <p class="dl-blurb">
      No sponsored order. Six axes, deterministic scoring, and a mixer that
      recomputes the board instantly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="dl-container" style="padding: 12px 16px 40px; max-width: 68ch;">
    <p style="color: #2C2C2C; margin: 8px 0 24px;">
      DeviceLab is a small, opinionated device ranker. We score every device
      on six axes and let you weight them yourself. This page is the
      contract for how that works.
    </p>

    <h2>Scoring</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Six axes: performance, portability, display, battery, build, value.</li>
      <li>Each axis is 0–100.</li>
      <li>The composite is a normalised weighted mean of your weights ×
        the device's axis scores.</li>
      <li>Value is derived from performance-per-£ min-max normalised across
        the whole catalogue — not editorial.</li>
      <li>Ties break on <span class="mono">value</span>, then alphabetically.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Nothing about the ranking depends on price feeds, affiliate
        offers, or sponsorship.</strong> If a merchant tries to pay for a
        higher rank, the answer is no. Ingestion sits in a separate module
        with a hard boundary to the scoring engine.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Personas</h2>
    <p>
      Six personas — Overall / Value / Creator / Gamer / Student / Business —
      are named weight vectors that prewire the mixer to what a specific
      shopper typically cares about. You can still slide any axis to override
      one; the moment you do, the persona flips to "Custom".
    </p>

    <h2>Retail links + commission</h2>
    <p>
      Buy buttons link to Amazon UK and (where available) the manufacturer's
      own store. Some of those links may earn us a commission — <strong>they
      never affect scores or ranking</strong>. Offers are sorted by delivered
      price only. Outbound clicks are logged so we can see which retailers
      actually convert and prioritise partnerships accordingly.
    </p>

    <h2>Price tracking</h2>
    <p>
      "Track price" opens an email capture that stores (email, device, target
      price) in Cloudflare KV. When the price pipeline lands, a scheduled job
      will diff incoming price points against saved targets and send at most
      one email per trigger. No newsletter.
    </p>

    <h2>Roadmap markers in the code</h2>
    <p>Four integration points are stubbed and marked in the codebase:</p>
    <ul class="mono" style="font-size: 13px;">
      <li>TODO(ingestion) — where the n8n price job writes offers + real priceHistory.</li>
      <li>TODO(affiliate) — where merchant links get GTIN-matched deep links + tracking params.</li>
      <li>TODO(alerts) — the scheduled consumer that emails matches on target prices.</li>
      <li>TODO(analytics) — swap CLICK_KV for Cloudflare Analytics Engine for SQL-shaped querying.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
